1097
00:50:50,384 --> 00:50:55,114
this layered structure here was only two layers high,

1098
00:50:55,854 --> 00:50:58,334
and we put in a particle over here

1099
00:50:58,334 --> 00:51:00,814
and took one out at the neighboring point.

1100
00:51:01,414 --> 00:51:05,664
Then there would be a contribution to the amplitude

1101
00:51:05,664 --> 00:51:09,914
of that coming from this term in the product,

1102
00:51:10,434 --> 00:51:12,534
phi of x times phi of neighboring x.

1103
00:51:12,534 --> 00:51:16,784
That would contribute, and it would contribute

1104
00:51:16,784 --> 00:51:21,034
to the amplitude, basically the factor minus i.

1105
00:51:21,714 --> 00:51:24,464
It would tell you that the amplitude to go from

1106
00:51:24,464 --> 00:51:27,214
one point to another was simply minus i, this coefficient here.

1107
00:51:28,514 --> 00:51:32,534
Okay, but that's not very good if this...

1108
00:51:38,194 --> 00:51:39,954
How do we get from here to here?

1109
00:51:41,194 --> 00:51:42,294
Okay, from here to here.

1110
00:51:42,374 --> 00:51:42,514
How do we get from here to here?

1111
00:51:42,514 --> 00:51:42,534
How do we get from here to here?

1112
00:51:42,534 --> 00:51:46,484
How do we get a particle from here to here and calculate the amplitude

1113
00:51:46,484 --> 00:51:50,434
that if we put in a particle over here, that will detect it over here?

1114
00:51:50,994 --> 00:51:56,234
For that, we have to find in this sum of products here,

1115
00:51:56,234 --> 00:52:01,474
we have to have a term which will leave no dangling ends.

1116
00:52:02,334 --> 00:52:04,414
Okay, let's just take this term here.

1117
00:52:06,494 --> 00:52:09,504
This has a particle moving from x to x prime,

1118
00:52:09,504 --> 00:52:12,514
and then another particle moving from x to x prime.

1119
00:52:12,534 --> 00:52:14,774
So we have x double prime to x triple prime.

1120
00:52:16,394 --> 00:52:20,574
Are you saying the second term contributes only

1121
00:52:20,574 --> 00:52:24,754
when the initial and final state are adjacent?

1122
00:52:25,594 --> 00:52:26,674
This term here, yeah.

1123
00:52:27,734 --> 00:52:28,714
Yeah, that's right.

1124
00:52:29,454 --> 00:52:31,454
This notation means

1125
00:52:31,454 --> 00:52:33,454
neighboring particles, neighboring boxes.

1126
00:52:34,554 --> 00:52:36,944
Here we have one neighboring box, and

1127
00:52:36,944 --> 00:52:39,334
here we have two other neighboring boxes.

1128
00:52:39,334 --> 00:52:39,814
Yeah.

1129
00:52:40,074 --> 00:52:42,494
So, for that we have the five x prime.

1130
00:52:42,494 --> 00:52:46,494
The first term is 5x 5x prime.

1131
00:52:46,494 --> 00:52:46,994
Yeah.

1132
00:52:46,994 --> 00:52:48,994
And the second term is 5 double prime.

1133
00:52:48,994 --> 00:52:53,124
Yeah, it just means pick two

1134
00:52:53,124 --> 00:52:57,254
neighboring and sum over all possibilities.

1135
00:52:58,073 --> 00:53:02,494
Sum, this is a sum over all neighboring pairs.

1136
00:53:02,494 --> 00:53:04,494
So it doesn't have to be adjacent to the first?

1137
00:53:04,494 --> 00:53:05,494
No, no, no, no.

1138
00:53:05,494 --> 00:53:07,494
In general not, but it can be.

1139
00:53:07,494 --> 00:53:09,523
In fact, this could even be the

1140
00:53:09,523 --> 00:53:11,553
same pair, but it doesn't have to be.

1141
00:53:11,553 --> 00:53:12,053
Yeah.

1142
00:53:12,054 --> 00:53:13,054
Sum over all of them.

1143
00:53:13,054 --> 00:53:15,054
All right, so what does this one do?

1144
00:53:15,054 --> 00:53:18,054
It moves a particle from x to x prime, and this

1145
00:53:18,054 --> 00:53:21,054
one moves a particle from x double prime to x triple prime.

1146
00:53:21,054 --> 00:53:22,054
All right.

1147
00:53:22,054 --> 00:53:23,054
So one of them moves

1148
00:53:23,054 --> 00:53:24,054
a particle from here to here.

1149
00:53:24,054 --> 00:53:26,554
This is x prime to x double,

1150
00:53:26,554 --> 00:53:29,054
to x, from x to x prime.

1151
00:53:29,054 --> 00:53:30,554
And then the other one moves

1152
00:53:30,554 --> 00:53:32,054
a particle from here to here.

1153
00:53:32,054 --> 00:53:35,054
That's x double prime and x triple prime, let's say.

1154
00:53:36,054 --> 00:53:40,054
Obviously there's going to be dangling ends.

1155
00:53:41,054 --> 00:53:42,054
Unless,

1156
00:53:42,054 --> 00:53:45,554
well, let's take this case here

1157
00:53:45,554 --> 00:53:49,054
where we only have three layers.

1158
00:53:49,054 --> 00:53:53,554
If we only have three layers, the only way to avoid dangling

1159
00:53:53,554 --> 00:53:58,054
ends is to have the first particle connected to the second particle,

1160
00:53:58,054 --> 00:54:01,554
sorry, the first box connected to the neighboring

1161
00:54:01,554 --> 00:54:05,054
box, and then this box connected to this box.

1162
00:54:05,054 --> 00:54:08,054
There won't be any dangling ends except for the dangling

1163
00:54:08,054 --> 00:54:11,054
ends which correspond to the initial particle and the final particle.

1164
00:54:11,054 --> 00:54:19,054
So if this was only three layers thick, we would find a

1165
00:54:19,054 --> 00:54:27,054
contribution here, namely where x prime is the same as x double prime,

1166
00:54:27,054 --> 00:54:32,554
that transports the particle from the initial position to the intermediate

1167
00:54:32,554 --> 00:54:38,054
position, and then from the intermediate position to the final position.

1168
00:54:38,054 --> 00:54:39,054
All right.

1169
00:54:39,054 --> 00:54:40,054
So,

1170
00:54:40,054 --> 00:54:41,054
let's look at this.

1171
00:54:41,054 --> 00:54:42,054
Okay.

1172
00:54:42,054 --> 00:54:44,554
What would be the amplitude then associated

1173
00:54:44,554 --> 00:54:47,054
with a particle going from here to here?

1174
00:54:47,054 --> 00:54:51,054
At least corresponding to this term, it would be

1175
00:54:51,054 --> 00:54:55,054
a one over two factorial and a minus sign.

1176
00:54:55,054 --> 00:54:56,054
That would be it.

1177
00:54:56,054 --> 00:54:58,554
You read off the coefficients, and

1178
00:54:58,554 --> 00:55:01,054
the coefficients tell you the amplitude.

1179
00:55:01,054 --> 00:55:03,054
Thus far, we don't have a

1180
00:55:03,054 --> 00:55:05,054
way to get from here to here.

1181
00:55:05,054 --> 00:55:08,054
Not with two factorials, but with two factorials.

1182
00:55:08,054 --> 00:55:09,054
Okay.

1183
00:55:09,054 --> 00:55:11,054
Not with two steps, anyway.

1184
00:55:11,054 --> 00:55:12,054
Two steps can...

1185
00:55:12,054 --> 00:55:18,554
However, if this was only two layers thick, we would have now

1186
00:55:18,554 --> 00:55:25,054
a way to get from here to here, to go across the diagonal.

1187
00:55:25,054 --> 00:55:27,054
How do we go across the diagonal?

1188
00:55:27,054 --> 00:55:30,554
We go again to this second order term here,

1189
00:55:30,554 --> 00:55:34,054
the term which has a two factorial in it,

1190
00:55:34,054 --> 00:55:35,554
and we find the term which

1191
00:55:35,554 --> 00:55:37,054
takes us from x to x.

1192
00:55:37,054 --> 00:55:42,054
From x to x prime, and then from x prime...

1193
00:55:42,054 --> 00:55:43,554
From x to x prime,

1194
00:55:43,554 --> 00:55:45,054
and then from x prime to...

1195
00:55:45,054 --> 00:55:52,054
From here to here, and then here to here.

1196
00:55:52,054 --> 00:55:53,054
What's that?

1197
00:55:53,054 --> 00:55:55,054
There are other paths.

1198
00:55:55,054 --> 00:55:56,054
There are other...

1199
00:55:56,054 --> 00:55:58,054
Other paths to get to this angle.

1200
00:55:58,054 --> 00:55:59,054
Yeah.

1201
00:55:59,054 --> 00:56:00,554
There's another path where you jump from

1202
00:56:00,554 --> 00:56:02,054
here first to here, and then up.

1203
00:56:02,054 --> 00:56:05,054
I don't think there's any other besides that.

1204
00:56:07,054 --> 00:56:08,054
Yeah.

1205
00:56:08,054 --> 00:56:09,054
Not with two...

1206
00:56:09,054 --> 00:56:10,054
Oh, not with just two terms.

1207
00:56:10,054 --> 00:56:11,054
Right.

1208
00:56:11,054 --> 00:56:12,054
Okay.

1209
00:56:12,054 --> 00:56:14,054
But now, there was no reason

1210
00:56:14,054 --> 00:56:16,054
to stop here with only two terms.

1211
00:56:16,054 --> 00:56:19,054
Let's go on.

1212
00:56:19,054 --> 00:56:21,054
We can have three terms.

1213
00:56:21,054 --> 00:56:24,554
Three terms would correspond to going

1214
00:56:24,554 --> 00:56:28,054
from one box to an adjacent box.

1215
00:56:28,054 --> 00:56:33,054
Well, it would correspond to three distinct steps.

1216
00:56:33,054 --> 00:56:34,554
And if those three distinct steps were

1217
00:56:34,554 --> 00:56:36,054
to connect it together in a row,

1218
00:56:36,054 --> 00:56:38,554
or to connect it together into a chain,

1219
00:56:38,554 --> 00:56:41,054
in other words, in this sum of products,

1220
00:56:41,054 --> 00:56:46,054
we found the term which took us...

1221
00:56:46,054 --> 00:56:50,054
Here, we could come right back again.

1222
00:56:50,054 --> 00:56:52,054
That would contribute together with the

1223
00:56:52,054 --> 00:56:54,054
direct jump from here to here,

1224
00:56:54,054 --> 00:56:56,554
would contribute to the amplitude to

1225
00:56:56,554 --> 00:56:59,054
go from this point to this point.

1226
00:56:59,054 --> 00:57:02,554
So you see, built into this prescription is

1227
00:57:02,554 --> 00:57:06,054
something like the original particle path integral idea.

1228
00:57:06,054 --> 00:57:08,554
The amplitude to get from here to here is the

1229
00:57:08,554 --> 00:57:11,054
sum over the amplitude to go from here to here,

1230
00:57:11,054 --> 00:57:13,554
and the amplitude to go through

1231
00:57:13,554 --> 00:57:16,054
another root, also this one back here.

1232
00:57:16,054 --> 00:57:21,054
And eventually, if you expand this out to arbitrary order,

1233
00:57:21,054 --> 00:57:26,054
there will be a term in there for every possible

1234
00:57:26,054 --> 00:57:31,054
root that you can take to go from any initial configuration

1235
00:57:31,054 --> 00:57:34,054
to any final configuration of that particle.

1236
00:57:34,054 --> 00:57:35,054
Okay.

1237
00:57:35,054 --> 00:57:39,554
So, first of all, just thinking

1238
00:57:39,554 --> 00:57:44,054
about a single particle moving in spacetime,

1239
00:57:44,054 --> 00:57:48,054
this field Lagrangian contains information

1240
00:57:48,054 --> 00:57:52,054
about the amplitudes to go from...

1241
00:57:52,054 --> 00:57:56,054
Now, let's take an arbitrary...

1242
00:57:56,054 --> 00:58:00,054
to go from any point to any other point.

1243
00:58:00,054 --> 00:58:01,554
What you do is you add up

1244
00:58:01,554 --> 00:58:03,054
all of the possible ways of going there,

1245
00:58:03,054 --> 00:58:06,054
and what is the coefficient

1246
00:58:06,054 --> 00:58:09,054
for each way of going there?

1247
00:58:09,054 --> 00:58:13,054
You read it off the coefficient that

1248
00:58:13,054 --> 00:58:17,054
multiplies that particular term in this sum.

1249
00:58:17,054 --> 00:58:21,054
1 over 2 factorial, 1 over 3 factorial.

1250
00:58:21,054 --> 00:58:23,054
Some of them have i's,

1251
00:58:23,054 --> 00:58:25,054
some of them don't have i's.

1252
00:58:25,054 --> 00:58:28,054
Remember that i squared is minus 1, so some of

1253
00:58:28,054 --> 00:58:31,054
them have i's and some of them don't have i's.

1254
00:58:31,054 --> 00:58:34,054
And so in general, the amplitude to go

1255
00:58:34,054 --> 00:58:37,054
from one point will be a complex number.

1256
00:58:37,054 --> 00:58:39,054
But they can also go back and forth.

1257
00:58:39,054 --> 00:58:40,554
That's what's new. That's one

1258
00:58:40,554 --> 00:58:42,054
of the things that's new here,

1259
00:58:42,054 --> 00:58:44,554
that they can propagate up and

1260
00:58:44,554 --> 00:58:47,054
down, and that's a feature of relativity.

1261
00:58:47,054 --> 00:58:52,054
Even the same two cells.

1262
00:58:52,054 --> 00:58:53,054
What's that?

1263
00:58:53,054 --> 00:58:55,054
Even the same two cells thousands of times.

1264
00:58:55,054 --> 00:58:57,054
Oh, indeed.

1265
00:58:57,054 --> 00:58:58,054
But you can go backwards.

1266
00:58:58,054 --> 00:58:59,054
Yeah.

1267
00:58:59,054 --> 00:59:00,054
All right.

1268
00:59:00,054 --> 00:59:06,054
Let's talk about going backward in time.

1269
00:59:06,054 --> 00:59:09,554
You could think of, here's

1270
00:59:09,554 --> 00:59:13,054
one that goes backward in time.

1271
00:59:13,054 --> 00:59:16,554
You can think of this as either allowing a

1272
00:59:16,554 --> 00:59:20,054
new rule where particles can go backward in time,

1273
00:59:20,054 --> 00:59:24,054
or you can follow time forward and say what really

1274
00:59:24,054 --> 00:59:28,054
happened here is the particle moved from here to here,

1275
00:59:28,054 --> 00:59:30,054
and then a particle pair,

1276
00:59:30,054 --> 00:59:32,054
particle and antiparticle in fact,

1277
00:59:32,054 --> 00:59:34,054
were created,

1278
00:59:34,054 --> 00:59:37,054
the particle half of it going to here,

1279
00:59:37,054 --> 00:59:40,054
and the antiparticle combining together

1280
00:59:40,054 --> 00:59:43,054
with the original particle to annihilate.

1281
00:59:43,054 --> 00:59:45,054
Think of it either way.

1282
00:59:45,054 --> 00:59:51,054
But the rule now allows trajectories which go backward.

1283
00:59:53,054 --> 00:59:57,054
Let's come back to this term here.

1284
01:00:00,054 --> 01:00:02,554
In this form of relation, since

1285
01:00:02,554 --> 01:00:05,054
you have n factorials in the denominator,

1286
01:00:05,054 --> 01:00:07,054
does this mean that you sort

1287
01:00:07,054 --> 01:00:09,054
of have convergence in the nulls?

1288
01:00:09,054 --> 01:00:11,054
Does it help the convergence?

1289
01:00:11,054 --> 01:00:17,054
Well, the n factorials certainly help the convergence,

1290
01:00:17,054 --> 01:00:19,054
but they're not enough to make it converge.

